description: "The word is made up of two kanji, gei (芸), meaning 'art', and sha (者), meaning 'person' or 'practitioner'. The most literal translation of geisha would be 'artist', 'person who makes art', or 'artisan'." Another name for geisha is geiko (芸 子), which is commonly used to refer to geisha in western Japan, a region that includes Kyoto."////SECOND PIECE FROM I HATE LOVING ROBOTS.////3000x3000 .png
